column5: Got out today for a few hours on Simcoe -- ended up finding some fish in 12-14 fow. They were extremely skiddish -- had to drag back 100feet plus to get them to bite.  Couldn't cast to them, they'd scatter.  Only gets better from here!  There were much bigger fish in the area...if we'd had more time we might've gotten some real bruisers!
Nice Kev.  Let me know if you need a hand getting your van stuck at the launch again this fall!  I'd be more the happy to help you with that!
Terry,he,s on our spot,get the boat ready. LOL  Nice fish Kev
Anyone know when the Big Boys start to bite ??
Prime time is late Oct into November imo...fish turn into complete footballs...  Enjoy!
